  "body": "While doing debugging for the peering for 4844 devnet5 with lodestar as bootnode, it was figured that lodestar couldn't seem to generate the correct ENR most probably because Network mode was `shared`\r\n\r\nFlags to start lodestar (from docker inspect) :```\r\n\"Args\": [\r\n            \"./packages/cli/bin/lodestar\",\r\n            \"beacon\",\r\n            \"--dataDir=/data\",\r\n            \"--listenAddress=0.0.0.0\",\r\n            \"--port=9000\",\r\n            \"--enr.ip=188.166.69.205\",\r\n            \"--enr.tcp=9000\",\r\n            \"--rest\",\r\n            \"--rest.address=0.0.0.0\",\r\n            \"--rest.port=5052\",\r\n            \"--jwt-secret=/execution-auth.jwt\",\r\n            \"--execution.urls=http://ethereumjs:8551\",\r\n            \"--metrics\",\r\n            \"--metrics.address=0.0.0.0\",\r\n            \"--metrics.port=5054\",\r\n            \"--paramsFile=/network-config/config.yaml\",\r\n            \"--genesisStateFile=/network-config/genesis.ssz\",\r\n            \"--network.connectToDiscv5Bootnodes\"\r\n        ],\r\n```\r\n\r\ngenerated ENR: ```\r\nenr:-LW4QFTTz_3Q-tVJJRaRUp1LY2eiS5ySkEz_iwwu9C8CQq87NoM5lj7nMGUU60qjBTB7qp2OdXSPGyRGUen_CxyaaAQLh2F0dG5ldHOIAAAAAAAAAACEZXRoMpBSRrDJQEhEBf__________gmlkgnY0iXNlY3AyNTZrMaEDhKvBbQfO2xcsGxsvMq1zpluaUfXhgASnmxlEqH5BNumIc3luY25ldHOIAAAAAAAAAACDdGNwgiMo\r\n```\r\n\r\nenr viewer:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76567250/233648339-181dea60-c98c-47b5-a75d-a44b3d70969e.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nExpected results: ENR should have correct, ip, udp and multiaddrs and peers should be able to connect\r\n\r\ncc @skylenet, @parithosh",
